{"parse":{"title":"Sociology of film","pageid":18611039,"revid":830555587,"text":{"*":"<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><p>The<b> sociology of film</b> deals with the <a href=\"/wiki/Sociological_analysis\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Sociological analysis\">sociological analysis</a> of film.<sup id=\"cite_ref-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup>  According to a university class in it, the field includes \"Contemporary cinema as a culture clue to social change; an introduction to the social forces involved in film-making in the United States and other cultures; the influence of films on mass and select audiences.\" <sup id=\"cite_ref-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup> According to another university course, it covers \"social aspects causes and consequences of the production, distribution, content, form and reception of film.\"<sup id=\"cite_ref-3\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p><i>The New York Times</i> said, \"One problem, though, is that if the audience is the measure all things, then art becomes a reflection of sociology and dissecting audience tastes becomes the art.\"<sup id=\"cite_ref-4\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-4\">&#91;4&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"References\">References</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Sociology_of_film&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" title=\"Edit section: References\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"reflist\" style=\"list-style-type: decimal;\">\n<div class=\"mw-references-wrap\"><ol class=\"references\">\n<li id=\"cite_note-1\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-1\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><cite class=\"citation journal\">Morris, Martin (Nov 1966). <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.journals.uchicago.edu/doi/abs/10.1086/224308\">\"&#91;Review of &#93; \"The Sociology of Film Art<span style=\"padding-right:0.2em;\">\"</span>\"</a>. <i><a href=\"/wiki/American_Journal_of_Sociology\" title=\"American Journal of Sociology\">American Journal of Sociology</a></i>. <b>73</b> (3): 314. <a href=\"/wiki/Digital_object_identifier\" title=\"Digital object identifier\">doi</a>:<a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"//doi.org/10.1086/224308\">10.1086/224308</a><span class=\"reference-accessdate\">. Retrieved <span class=\"nowrap\">5 March</span> 2017</span>.</cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.genre=article&amp;rft.jtitle=American+Journal+of+Sociology&amp;rft.atitle=%5BReview+of+%5D+%22The+Sociology+of+Film+Art%22&amp;rft.volume=73&amp;rft.issue=3&amp;rft.pages=314&amp;rft.date=1966-11&amp;rft_id=info%3Adoi%2F10.1086%2F224308&amp;rft.aulast=Morris&amp;rft.aufirst=Martin&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.journals.uchicago.edu%2Fdoi%2Fabs%2F10.1086%2F224308&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ASociology+of+film\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"display:none;\">&#160;</span></span></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-2\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-2\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><cite class=\"citation web\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://bulletin.hofstra.edu/preview_course_nopop.php?catoid=59&amp;coid=138010\">\"SOC 112 The Sociology of Film\"</a>. <i>Hofstra University Bulletin</i><span class=\"reference-accessdate\">. Retrieved <span class=\"nowrap\">5 March</span> 2017</span>.</cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.genre=unknown&amp;rft.jtitle=Hofstra+University+Bulletin&amp;rft.atitle=SOC+112+The+Sociology+of+Film&amp;rft_id=https%3A%2F%2Fbulletin.hofstra.edu%2Fpreview_course_nopop.php%3Fcatoid%3D59%26coid%3D138010&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2F